<task id="002" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>BFF DTO — Add `AttachmentDriveItemIds` canonical field + non-breaking alias mapping</title>
    <phase>Wave 0 — Foundations + Non-Breaking BFF</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>001</dependencies>
    <blocks>005, 007</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, refactoring, communication</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Modifies `.cs` files in `Sprk.Bff.Api`; non-breaking contract change with mapping logic; must respect ADR-010 / ADR-019 / ADR-024 and the bff-extensions governance checklist</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <fr-refs>FR-21</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Add `public string[]? AttachmentDriveItemIds { get; init; }` as the canonical attachment field on `SendCommunicationRequest`, mark the existing `AttachmentDocumentIds` `[Obsolete("Use AttachmentDriveItemIds")]`, and implement non-breaking server-side mapping in `CommunicationService` so existing callers continue to work during the R3 migration window. Both fields MUST be accepted; canonical wins when both are populated; alias usage logs a deprecation warning. Update XML docs on both fields to clarify Microsoft Graph `driveItem` ID semantics (NOT `sprk_document` GUIDs).

    This is the BFF half of the field rename. The client wrapper update happens in task 005 (depends on this). Per FR-21 + NFR-05, this MUST be non-breaking — all existing callers continue to work unmodified.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Spaarke BFF engineer. Authoritative on `Services/Communication/` pipeline. Familiar with ADR-010 (DI minimalism via `CommunicationModule`), ADR-019 (ProblemDetails), ADR-024 (polymorphic resolver), and the binding `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` governance checklist for BFF additions.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `SendCommunicationRequest` exposes both `AttachmentDriveItemIds` (canonical) and `AttachmentDocumentIds` (deprecated alias). `CommunicationService.SendAsync()` normalizes the two into a single internal list at entry. When both are set, the canonical field wins and a structured warning is logged. When only the alias is set, it is copied to the canonical slot and a deprecation warning is logged. Build is clean; `dotnet test` passes; bff-extensions placement justification stated in PR description.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Empirical finding from project pre-flight (CLAUDE.md row 3): `SendCommunicationRequest.cs` currently exposes ONLY `AttachmentDocumentIds`. The name is misleading — those values are Graph `driveItem` IDs, not `sprk_document` GUIDs. DocumentEmailWizard at line 494 ships `sprk_document` GUIDs into this field, which is the latent bug class to be closed across R3 (Wave 5 task 075 fixes the caller; task 002 here cleans up the DTO).

      Per FR-21 + NFR-05, the rename MUST be non-breaking. R4 will remove the alias after all callers have migrated. This task only adds the alias path — it does NOT delete or rename the deprecated field.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Communication/Models/SendCommunicationRequest.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Communication/CommunicationService.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Api/CommunicationEndpoints.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Infrastructure/DI/CommunicationModule.cs</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="project">FR-21: non-breaking rename — both `AttachmentDriveItemIds` and `AttachmentDocumentIds` MUST be accepted by the BFF DTO. R4 removes the alias; R3 does NOT.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">NFR-05: existing client callers MUST NOT break. Existing requests sending `AttachmentDocumentIds` continue to send mail successfully.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Server-side mapping rule: if `AttachmentDocumentIds` set AND `AttachmentDriveItemIds` null → copy across. If BOTH set → prefer canonical AND log a structured warning (caller bug, but proceed).</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">Communication services register via `CommunicationModule` only. Do NOT add new DI registrations outside that module.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-019">Validation failures surface as ProblemDetails (existing pattern). This task adds no new error path; it normalizes input at entry to `SendAsync()`.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-024">Server-side `IncomingAssociationResolver` is unchanged. This task touches only outbound DTO + the outbound mapping step.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">bff-extensions.md placement justification REQUIRED in PR description even though answer is "in BFF" (per CLAUDE.md §10).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Publish-size delta MUST be reported (per CLAUDE.md §10 bullet 4; baseline ~45.65 MB as of 2026-05-26). This task adds zero packages; delta expected ≈ 0.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-033">The new ADR (task 001) codifies the canonical pattern. Confirm this task aligns.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/plan.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/endpoint-definition.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/api/endpoint-filters.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-010-di-minimalism.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-019-problemdetails-error-responses.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-024-polymorphic-resolver-pattern.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-033-communication-architecture.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/communication-service-architecture.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="DTO field obsoletion (non-breaking)" location="docs/architecture/communication-service-architecture.md">
        Mark old field `[Obsolete("Use X")]`; keep accepting it; normalize at single entry point in service layer; log structured warning on use.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="bff-extensions placement decision" location=".claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md">
        State placement decision explicitly in PR description, citing decision criteria from bff-extensions.md, even when answer is "stays in BFF."
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `SendCommunicationRequest.cs` to confirm current shape (only `AttachmentDocumentIds` per empirical finding #3).</step>
    <step order="2">Read `CommunicationService.cs` to locate `SendAsync()` entry point and identify where to insert the normalization shim.</step>
    <step order="3">Read `.claude/constraints/bff-extensions.md` §F (Test update obligation, Asymmetric-Registration, Fixture-Config-FIRST) — this task does NOT add a conditional service, but the test update obligation still applies (task 008 covers tests; PR for 002 must indicate tests will follow in 008).</step>
    <step order="4">Edit `SendCommunicationRequest.cs`: add `public string[]? AttachmentDriveItemIds { get; init; }` with XML doc clarifying "Microsoft Graph driveItem IDs (NOT `sprk_document` GUIDs). Canonical field per ADR-033." Mark existing `AttachmentDocumentIds` with `[Obsolete("Use AttachmentDriveItemIds. This alias will be removed in R4 (FR-21).")]` and update its XML doc to point to `AttachmentDriveItemIds` and note the deprecation.</step>
    <step order="5">Edit `CommunicationService.SendAsync()`: at the top of the method (after request validation, before Graph call), add a normalization block: if `request.AttachmentDriveItemIds is null && request.AttachmentDocumentIds is { Length: > 0 }` → copy `AttachmentDocumentIds` into a local canonical list AND `_logger.LogWarning("Caller used deprecated AttachmentDocumentIds field. Migrate to AttachmentDriveItemIds (FR-21).")`. If both set → use `AttachmentDriveItemIds` AND `_logger.LogWarning("Caller sent both AttachmentDocumentIds and AttachmentDriveItemIds; using canonical AttachmentDriveItemIds.")`. Below this block, replace any subsequent direct reads of `request.AttachmentDocumentIds` with the local canonical variable.</step>
    <step order="6">Run `dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` — confirm build clean (obsolete-field usage will produce CS0618 warnings in the SAME file, suppress with `#pragma warning disable CS0618` around the normalization read, scoped narrowly).</step>
    <step order="7">Run `dotnet test tests/unit/Sprk.Bff.Api.Tests/ --filter Communication` — confirm existing tests still pass. (New unit tests added in task 008.)</step>
    <step order="8">Run `dotnet publish -c Release src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/ -o c:/tmp/r3-002-publish/` and report compressed size + delta vs baseline (~45.65 MB). Expected ≈ 0 MB delta. Record in task notes/ if &gt;0.5 MB.</step>
    <step order="9">Run `dotnet list package --vulnerable --include-transitive` — confirm no new HIGH-severity CVEs.</step>
    <step order="9.5">FULL-rigor quality gates: invoke `code-review` skill on the diff; invoke `adr-check` skill against `spec.md`. Address any Critical findings.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 002 ✅ completed; confirm task 005 + task 007 dependencies satisfied.</step>
    <step order="11">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol: status → completed; advance to next pending task; record decisions (e.g., chosen canonical-prefer-with-warning vs canonical-prefer-silent).</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="read">Inspect current DTO + service shape</tool>
    <tool name="edit">Add canonical field + obsolete attribute + normalization shim</tool>
    <tool name="bash">Build, test, publish-size measurement, CVE scan</tool>
    <tool name="code-review">FULL-rigor quality gate at step 9.5</tool>
    <tool name="adr-check">FULL-rigor quality gate at step 9.5</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Communication/Models/SendCommunicationRequest.cs (UPDATED — canonical field + obsolete alias)</output>
    <output type="code">src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Communication/CommunicationService.cs (UPDATED — normalization shim + deprecation warnings)</output>
