  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`SendCommunicationRequest.AttachmentDriveItemIds` property exists (init-only, nullable `string[]?`).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`SendCommunicationRequest.AttachmentDocumentIds` has `[Obsolete("Use AttachmentDriveItemIds...")]` attribute.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">XML docs on both fields explicitly say "Microsoft Graph driveItem IDs" (not "document IDs").</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`CommunicationService.SendAsync()` normalizes both fields into one internal canonical list at entry.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">When only `AttachmentDocumentIds` is sent, the send proceeds AND a deprecation warning is logged (verifiable via test in task 008).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">When both fields are set, canonical wins AND a warning is logged.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`dotnet build src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/` succeeds with zero new errors/warnings outside the scoped `#pragma warning disable CS0618` region.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Existing `dotnet test` Communication-related tests still pass.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Publish-size delta reported in PR description; ≤ +0.5 MB expected.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No new HIGH-severity CVEs introduced.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    R4 will delete `AttachmentDocumentIds` after all callers (R3 + any external API consumers) have migrated. Track this in `projects/_backlog/needs-a-project.md` if not already on the R4 candidate list.

    Empirical finding context (CLAUDE.md row 3): only `AttachmentDocumentIds` is currently present. Confirmed at pre-flight 2026-06-05.

    Unit tests for the mapping behavior live in task 008 (parallel-group B in Wave 0). This task's acceptance criteria reference those tests but do NOT block on them — task 008 verifies; task 002 implements.

    DocumentEmailWizard line 494 bug (sending `sprk_document` GUIDs instead of driveItem IDs) is fixed in Wave 5 task 075. The deprecation warning here will fire from that caller until the migration lands.
  </notes>

